OL,4,CBoris Johnson promises more school
OL,5,Ccatch-up cash in 'damp squib' row
OL,6, The prime minister has promised schools
OL,7, in England there will be "more coming
OL,8, through" after catch-up funding plans
OL,9, were accused of being a "damp squib".
OL,11,FHead teachers had said they were
OL,12,F"hugely disappointed" by a #1.4bn Covid
OL,13,Frecovery package, which breaks down to
OL,14,F#50 extra per pupil per year.
OL,16,FMost of the funding will be for
OL,17,Ftutoring to make up for lost learning.
OL,19,FBoris Johnson said it would "give
OL,20,Fparents the confidence" that their
OL,21,Fchildren would be supported.
